"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The code attempts to set the x-axis major locator to MonthLocator() after setting the x-ticks to unique dates from the DataFrame. This can lead to a mismatch between the ticks and the locator, as MonthLocator is designed to work with a specific frequency of months rather than arbitrary dates. The x-ticks should be set after the locator is defined.\", \"patch\": \"17c17\\n< ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\\n---\\n> ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(MonthLocator())\\n> ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\"}"